<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n01119a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01119a">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01119a"> 119(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hat check ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Now Germany is <font color="green">[teeming]</font> with &ldquo;steptanzers&rdquo; which is German for clogdancers. Most of the youths, after demobilisation following the Armistice, learned &ldquo;steptanzering&rdquo; by mail from a correspondence school, run by a couple of soft-shoe American dancers, operating from Berlin <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The male &ldquo;steptanzers&rdquo; frequently help the <mark>hat-check</mark> bandits assisting patrons into their overcoats, thus collecting a few tips. <small> <a name="IT27jan23" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IT27jan23"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (27 January 1923) 6/7 [German Cabaret Craze. / By Henry Wales. / Essen, Friday.]</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05168b" href="c05all.htm#c05168b">VI.C.05:168(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
